DataElement.preferredDefinition: The 0 decimal place microliter numeric laboratory value representing the upper level of the normal range of values of mucosal-associated invariant T-cells in a specimen.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Mucosal-Associated Invariant T-Cell Laboratory Procedure Performed
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A T-cell subtype bearing a semi-invariant T-cell receptor and restricted by the major histocompatibility complex related molecule MR1. These cells occupy peripheral tissues and are noted for their reactivity against various microorganisms of either bacterial or fungal origin._Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting._Executed and carried through to completion.
